HadoopOps Technology Add-on
----------------------------------------
	Author: Splunk
	Version/Date: 04/08/2013
	Source type(s): vmstat, iostat, ps, top, df, cpu, hadoop_dfsreport,
        hadoop_fsckreport
	Input requirements: Hadoop metrics data through servlets needs manual
        setup, as described below
	Has index-time operations: true, this TA must be deployed on indexers
	Supported platform(s): 
		 * Apache 1.0.3
		 * Hortonworks Data Platform
		 * Coudera's Distribution CDH3

Using this Technology Add-on:
----------------------------------------
	Configuration: Automatic generation, with interactive management interface
	Scripted input setup: Automatic, except hadoopmon_metrics.sh
	
    Setup Hadoop metrics collection through servlet:
    -----------------------------------------------------
    * Pre-requisites: have command'curl' or 'wget' installed
    * Edit "local/inputs.conf" and create one stanza for each servlet url. The
        stanza name should be of the format:

        [script://.bin/hadoopmon_metrics.sh <full url to the servlet>

        The url can contain query parameters. When specifying query parameters,
        special characters need to be escaped by preceding each with a
        backslash. Special characters include questionmark (?), equal sign (=),
        hash (#), ampersand (&), star (*), and square brackets ([]).

        An example of hadoopmon_metrics.sh scripted input is shown below.

        ==== <local/inputs.conf> ====================================
        [script://./bin/hadoopmon_metrics.sh http://127.0.0.1:50070/jmx\?qry\=Hadoop:\*]
        disabled = 0
        interval = 10
        sourcetype = hadoop_metrics
        index = hadoopmon_metrics
        
        [script://./bin/hadoopmon_metrics.sh http://127.0.0.1:50090/metrics]
        disabled = 0
        interval = 10
        sourcetype = hadoop_metrics
        index = hadoopmon_metrics
	
